What is data modeling in Power BI?

Data modeling in Power BI is the process of creating a logical representation of your data to facilitate analysis and visualization. It involves defining relationships between tables, creating measures, and establishing data hierarchies. This enables users to easily navigate and analyze complex data sets. Effective data modeling is crucial for delivering actionable insights in Power BI.
